                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Hi.  My name is Zarlox Manastorm, and I'm a bad charm soloer.
<br />
/pause for applause
<br />
Admission is the first step towards recovery, eh?
<br />
Well, now that we got that out of the way, it's time to get to the basics.  Why am I so bad at charm soloing?  I mean, I know not to charm mobs that summon (after last night at least, but let's not elaborate), I always keep arcane rune up and my charisma is over 200.  I'm always on my toes, yet I always wind up in PoK shortly after my attempts to charm solo.  No, I'm not hasting my pet.  Yes, I'm slowing my target.  No, I don't forget to tash my pet (well...most of the time).
<br />
Additional information:
<br />
I'm level 64, use CoD, and tried charm soloing using Frogs in PoS (which didn't turn out well) and using assorted Diaku in Tactics (which didn't turn out well either).  I'm pretty stumped as to why I suck at this.  I suppose it's because charm soloing is more of an aquired ability - I kick ass and take names while grouping, which is what I've done for the past 64 levels, as I haven't taken much time to give charm soloing a try.
<br />
Any input you guys have would be greatly appreciated,
<br />
Thanks-
