                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I rarely solo charm anymore but from my past experiences it can be very frustrating.  Sometimes charm can be very painful when you just can't seem to keep a pet for more than 10seconds but I think you just need to keep trying.  
<br />

<br />
I would suggest for a start get a druid or ranger partner and head to HoH, any snarer will generally work reasonably well and with them charming is pretty much as safe as you can get.  As you get used to it more you probably won't need partners but if your having troubles I would at least for the first few times.  Get them to harmony one mob and pull the other one, tash him up and snare then charm, you may need to mezz if it resists snare or something but shouldn't be too hard.  Send pet into the remaining mob don't tash too early and pull agro off pet its a little like having a warrior build agro, the longer pet is fighting the more you can do without getting chased.  Get partner to snare mob you are fighting and also root it, slow and sit back let your pet work.
<br />
I always sit as far away from my pet as possible so that you have more time to react.  When your pet breaks I usually just mezzed and tash / snare / recharm but is various ways you can do it.  The mob your fighting should still be rooted so you only have to worry about pet, if it breaks it will be snared so can reroot.  Sow helps alot, if your not with partner can use wolf illusion (is seperate post about that).  The good thing about HoH is that you have alot of room to get away from the mobs you are fighting.  You will probably still die as things do go wrong but hopefully you will have better success and more fun <img src="images/smiles/icon_razz.gif" alt="icon_razz.gif" border="0" />   As you get more comfortable with the way charm works you can do it in other places too, Tactics is similar in the safe halls up the top but is a little less room altho you can run around the wall and stuff like that.
<br />

<br />
Hope that helps, Good luck  <img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="icon_wink.gif" border="0" /></span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=2541" target="_blank" class="postlink">Ruilen SilverThorn</a>
<br />
<a href="http://www.coldfuryguild.com" target="_blank" class="postlink">Cold Fury</a>
<br />
Quellious</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
