                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Much of this might not be helpful, since I'm nowhere near your level, but I thought I'd post what I've learned in my short time charm soloing.
<br />

<br />
First of all, never give up.  The first time I really began charming, it took me almost 4 hours to get a feel for it.  During those four hours, I died twice, and zoned more times than I can count (which, in turn, caused me to sleepwalk out of my bedroom that night, thinking I was still trying to clear aggro  <img src="images/smiles/icon_redface.gif" alt="icon_redface.gif" border="0" /> ).  That day was really frustrating for me.  There were a handful of times that I thought about calling it quits for the day, but I kept at it, and I ended up getting it down.
<br />

<br />
The other thing that was touched on earlier, is that charm is stupid.  It makes no sense why a pet will last 5 minutes before breaking, and another will break 6 or 7 times in that same period.  When this happens, I either keep re-charming, or mez/root and grab a new pet.  It may not be the best solution, but it makes me feel better.  <img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="icon_wink.gif" border="0" /> 
<br />

<br />
Hope this has been somewhat useful.  Good luck.  <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" /></span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Riothamus</span>
<br />
Beguiler
<br />
&lt;The Warders of Tri Lith&gt;
<br />
Zebuxoruk</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
