                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">People have already said most things, so let me just add:
<br />

<br />
PoS is a bad place to solo, because nearly everything summons.  You don't want your pet OR your target to summon.  It can be dealt with, but it adds considerably to the risk.
<br />

<br />
Diaku's are not good pets in tactics.  They can be okay, but they have a higher MR than anything in the pit (Zek Initiates are my personal favorite pet).  Higher MR translates pretty directly to shorter charm times (and thus more dying).
<br />

<br />
As silly as it sounds, pretend you're level 20 again, and go to East Karana.  Load the spells you would have at that level, and pretend that if you take 200 damage you 'died'.  Get used to recharming.  Once you've got a feel for that, try again in a higher level area.  I would say of the planes, HoH is probably the easiest zone to charm in.  PoNightmare can be done pretty well, and PoV wasteland is pretty good also.  Tactics is a bit tougher due to less space/indoor/higher MR.
<br />

<br />
Search around on this board, there is a lot of info about spots to charm.
<br />

<br />
If you find EK too easy, try again somewhere like lower guk.  See how long you can keep frenzy or AM broken.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Eleandra
<br />
<a href="http://www.scienceofwar.net" target="_blank">www.scienceofwar.net</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
