                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I totally agree with the above post...and I tell the same to any chanters looking for help..go somewhere safe and practice. Then practice some more...it is worth the time. If that means Crushbone then so be it...this is a skill that takes time to aquire, and why learn on the killers?
<br />

<br />
My keys are a rooted pet to START..yes pull with tash then mez/root...buff as you like..I always snake click and NDT them..then get your mob to kill. Bring the soon to be mush bad guy with tash and root him on top of your pet. Back away..slow the bad guy and you are gtg. Keep the target mob rooted at all times, and when root wears off pet ...keep him targetted. I have Blue Ceramic Band to get a smidgen of damage in..and then wait while pet does the hard owrk. Med from as far away as you can, and it should see plenty of xp coming your way. If charm breaks...it is your choice. I usually have time to recharm with my ER4 Wand, but if not just root it and recharm...then nuke bad guy to break root and pull on top of pet again. You can not have two mobs beating on you if at least one is always rooted.
<br />

<br />
TD 3 has been a huge advantage...and of course level is always key...but really..get out there and work at it. I recommend not using in group setting until you are comfortable..but when you are great things will come your way.
<br />

<br />
Please send me a /tell in game if you want to talk..I am always open to helping out.
<br />

<br />
&lt;edit&gt; With respect to WoM..I find it a great spell in group setting..with mezzes flying, but solo it is easier to root/mezz/recharm on a break I find. Don't have it memmed either for solo..always in group../shrug
<br />

<br />

<br />
Tayemm Initio
<br />
Coercer Mith Marr</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
