                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">It is an acquired skill/ability that flourishes with practice...
<br />

<br />
That said there are a few recommendations I would have for you (probably stated above by my colleagues but I didn't read thru all of them because I wanted to put in my 2cp). 
<br />

<br />
1. Seperation is your greatest ally. Usually this means giving yourself enough room to either immediately recharm (not my personal favorite) or enough room to retash your pet and be ready to WoM (or stun if you have the new ldon stun) and then recharm. 
<br />

<br />
2. Root is almost always required (IMHO)... Keep that target mob rooted, it's bad enough dealing, potentially) with a hasted quadding dual wielding mage toys pet ... dealing with the mob it was beating on only makes it worse.  That said, if your rooting the target mob then don't be dumb and have NDT on your pet ... that proc breaks root alot 
<br />

<br />
3. SoW/SoE is nifty ! But shared greater wolf form and permanent illusion is better... the faster you are the easier it is to make seperation space when recharming or dealing with adds/breaks.
<br />

<br />
4. Blue Ceramic Band .. you only need to do 1pt of damage to get the majority of exp for the target mobs death... why waste a spell slot on a nuke when you can get all u need from the right clickable band... Initially mana and spell slots will likely be at a premium for you anyway.
<br />

<br />
5. Learn Thy Partner! There are alot of classes that can duo with a charming enchanter and add value to the 2 man group. The top 3 among those classes (IMHO) are Druids, Rangers, and Clerics. Druids & Rangers have ensnare which outlast any single casting of CoD.. druids heal better than rangers but rangers can generally put out more sustained dps than druids in charm duoing situations. While clerics lack snare they do have advantages that make them worthwhile as well including better, faster, more mana efficient heals, 2 different single target stuns that work on mobs up to 65, and of course... rez because I don't care how good you are you WILL die sometimes. 
<br />

<br />
6. Thru trial and error .. learn your marks... Practice and experiment, learn and adapt. Pets that summon are bad and usually so are zones with lots of summoning mobs. Wide open safe spaces are nice but learn how to handle enclosed areas too.
<br />

<br />
Some advice for you... I don't know how it is on your server but on FRo PoV isn't packed every night anymore. Learn to work on your CoD charming here in my opinion. The NE corner (i think.. been a while) has some relatively open areas with a good supply of mobs near by. Golems make good pets and aren't hugely MR. Additionally this will give you practice with unrootable mobs as some of the spiders are immune. Keep up soe or sow/wolf form + levitate... if in trouble don't stand there and die .. RUN over the cliff, zone out to clear aggro, evaluate what happened and how you could have done better ... go back and continue conquering. Daiku in Tactics make fairly poor pets .... get a gladiator, zek initiate, frenzied zek initiate (very dangerous hard hitting pet &lt;3 yummy !), or grab a druid partner and charm boars. 
<br />

<br />
As you work up your aa points the first thing i'd recommend is Eldritch Rune 3 ... that aa will save your proverbial arse more than just about any other. After that my personal recommendation is Total Domination 3... others may not have a very high opinion of this skill but I haven't had any personal experiences to lead me to believe it is anything other than golden in my book.
<br />

<br />
My last word of advice is ... ALWAYS make efforts to befriend clerics.. that kei you give a passing cleric today may be the connected to the rez you get tomorrow.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Microphenus Minimeat
<br />
Coercer
<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=746268" target="_blank" class="postlink">Stuff that would have rotted if I hadn't taken it</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
