                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Great post micro. I just want to add a few things. For me, I went through different phases of charm soloing. In my early stage, charming was lots of fun but quite risky and down time was alot but it does get better .... quite significantly. Assuming you are level 64/65, I will list the factors that made me better charm soloer.
<br />

<br />
1. Mana: SCM3, Mana Preserve 4, FT items, mana/int items, MC aa and GM aa. I did not have any of these when I started charm solo and had to med after each charm session. Now, I just chain charm solo. I always had high CHA (250+) so most of the pet lasts full duration.
<br />

<br />
2. TD: Nice to have but not essential. Saves mana in the long run. You always need to be ready for early break anyway so can't really depend on this.
<br />

<br />
3. Spell Haste 4: Because of this, I don't have to mez before charming. I can just tash, run and charm it ... saves some mana.
<br />

<br />
4. Defensive aa and hp items: Helps in group charming in tight space. But when charm soloing, you don't want to get hit ... ever. But helps in emergency situation.
<br />

<br />
5. Partner: With right partner, charming becomes "safe". My favorite is bard friend Iluvdar (BB). He pulls, mez, snares, fd, paci, dots ... Honestly, charm duoing with him is easier than being a primary slower.
<br />

<br />
6. Location: HoH was best for me. Not flagged to Tactics but love to try there. I don't really recommend South Hero Shrine to beginners. Instead, try NE or NW crypt. Alot bigger space to run around. Avoid sentries until you are comfortable dealing with them as they are not rootable or snarable.
<br />

<br />
7. WoM timing: If you have no space to run around and both your hasted ex-pet and mob is running toward you, time your WoM well then both will be mezed before hitting you. It takes quite a practice but it is a rez saver.
<br />

<br />
8. exp enhancer:
<br />
a. haste your pet when you are comforable dealing with it
<br />
b. use ceramic blue band to deal dmg to your target so you don't lose too much exp.
<br />
c. use shiftless deeds instead of forlorn deeds to save your mana. Time your slow so that by the time you have to kill your ex-pet, it will have less than 10% hp.
<br />

<br />
I still don't have good equipment because I am not in a raiding guild but I can still chain charm solo. Just wanted to encourage you that charming does get better, yields excellent experience and adds a whole new dimension to your exp group and even to your raids. And yes, your non-hasted BoT pet can out damage your whole group easily  <img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="icon_wink.gif" border="0" /> . One more thing. Don't believe everything you see on the forum. Check it out for yourself if you doubt it. It may kill you but you may learn something very useful from it.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=664034" target="_blank" class="postlink">Primer</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
