                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I'm only lvl 54 atm moment and just started charming in Pod at the fly camp but almost all of those 54lvls are by charm soloing and one thing to keep in mind is that, one of the big differences between the soloing chanter and grouping chanter is that the grouping chanter is used to trying to channel through a stun/mez or root when a break happens or when a mob is on him until mob is back under control or peeled off. 
<br />

<br />
    Whereas a soloer tends to kite the mob back under control well I do anyway, there was a brief period from beguile to Cajoling Whispers where I had to reroot mob to recharm, but now that I got Boltrans which is a 4 second cast compared to CWs 5.5 and Allures 6 second cast time I can recharm on the fly again.
<br />

<br />
   There's some great stuff here I would just like to reinforce a point made earlier, The comment on root parking your potential charmed victim is a great way to avoid early charm breaks I always use best root on mob Im charming then just root park pulled mob on top or right by charmed pet.
<br />

<br />
