                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Spell Haste IV (Ornate Boots) and Extended Range IV (Ceramic Sword of War) probably have the biggest impact on charming with CoD. Also, when you get a Virtue, also get a BoR (Blessing of Revernence), it will further haste your spells.
<br />

<br />
Getting off that charm/tash/root at a greater distance, faster makes all the difference....
<br />

<br />
I learned this VERY quickly in PoTactics. Took a group down the hall and the cleric blew a stun on a charm break. My pet took me down very fast, and then the cleric. The rest of the group didn't have agro yet or just FD'd.
<br />

<br />
I put up my buffs and then went back to get my pet (a very buffed up Diaku Raider). Pacification on the mob next to him, tash and run...
<br />

<br />
... "Wow!, he got really close to me before charm landed"...
<br />

<br />
... "Wow! Charm broke pretty fast!"...
<br />

<br />
... "Wow! I'm dead again!"...
<br />

<br />
I've done so many AA charm soloing (180 or so of my 196 AA) that I sometimes forget how vulnerable I am, especially with no gear.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=166364" target="_blank" class="postlink">Sage Craftah</a> - Master of all languages and tradeskills.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
