                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Eh, not really.
<br />

<br />
1. Pacify one.
<br />

<br />
2. Mez, Tash, Slow, Charm the other.
<br />

<br />
3. Sic charmed one on pacified one.
<br />

<br />
4. Keep root on pacified one.  Once every 40 health of your pet drops is often enough in most cases IMO.
<br />

<br />
5. Refresh root when the pet gets ~14-15% health.
<br />

<br />
6. Break charm at 3-4%
<br />

<br />
(Optional: Root ex-pet--does not apply to mobs immune to root)
<br />

<br />
7.  Nuke ex-pet just once with Insanity (unless of course it resists).
<br />

<br />
100% XP kill.  Extremely low risk.
<br />

<br />
Pacify and get another pet, and repeat till either the target mob dies or is so low that you may as well nuke it dead.  
<br />

<br />
If you feel it's too slow you can aggro a new one over earlier at like 50% pet health and mez it in preparation for a fresh slowed pet.  If charm breaks while you're getting the next pet ready, it's not nearly as bad channeling a spell through a slowed mob.  If root breaks while you're getting the next pet ready, the mob that's currently engaged won't give a damn unless you spammed it with like 10 tashes.  And if both break during this time, it's no worse than if the same happened using any other charm method, except that you only have one normal speed mob to channel through, not two, and you have the benefit of distance in some cases.
<br />

<br />
You can get 100% XP kills all the way through that way, or take a little less XP every 3 or 4 kills if you feel it is not worth it to squeeze 100% from every mob, and the most strenuous things you have to do is keep root on the mob you're fighting and channel a CoD on a slowed mob if you need to recharm.
<br />

<br />
This is, of course, not advised if the mobs proc things that break root or on things that can't be rooted, like the named suits of armor in Left Hero Shrine, but it is the absolute safest way IMO to kill off mobs that don't proc, like the Valorians, and it's the safest way I've found of getting rid of Valorian Sentries when there's just too many of them in the area you're camping.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Edit:</span>In my sleep-drugged state, I failed to remember that not every chanter necessarily has the funds to invest in a Boots of the Mosquito or a Goblin Gazughi Ring.  In those cases, yes, it's a bit more annoying to time breaks since there's the casting time of Invis involved.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Sleeping for 65 nights (with 167 interruptions...)
<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=467231" target="_blank" class="postlink">ZZZzzzzzz...</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
