                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">
<br />
 
<br />
Most everything has already been said but I saw a few GLARING errors that id like to talk about. 
<br />
 </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
I'm going to have to side with some of the other chanters on this. These are not the most efficient plans for charming, and possibly not the safest either. 
<br />

<br />
1. Keep the mob you are fighting ROOTED AT ALL TIMES. 
<br />
--- I personally don't like to root while charming, but I'm not going to argue that it doesn't make things a lot safer and is a valid tactic.
<br />

<br />
2. Do not slow the mob you are fighting unless necessary. 
<br />
--- Also a matter of personal preference, I prefer to keep my pet as long as possible and tash and slow every enemy.
<br />

<br />
3. Do not haste your pet if you are soloing. 
<br />
--- Always always always haste your pet, and if he can dual wield hand him weapon too. I generally kill 4-5 things before my pet is low on health, and kill them a lot faster than one who hasn't been hasted. Then break charm and kill pet. When it comes to soloing for exp, haste is your friend
<br />

<br />
4. Use insanity and slow to keep the fight as close as possible. 
<br />
--- Conserve your mana, don't be nuking constantly, when your going for Max XP (fast kills) you want to conserve your mana. Occasionally I will slow late on my last target to make sure my pet is wounded enough for me to kill it, but every bit of mana I save means I can continue pulling longer without medding which means more XP.
<br />

<br />
5. Make your pet win by the tiniest margin then kill your pet. 
<br />
--- True but only after he has wiped out 4 or 5 other mobs first. When it's time to dump the pet, you want him near death so you can finish it off with as little mana as possible. 
<br />

<br />
6. Keep yourself sowed at ALL times. 
<br />
--- Absolutely true, and get permanent illusion ASAP! Scaled wolf yourself and never ever go back. 
<br />

<br />
7. DONT RE-USE PETS SOLOING. 
<br />
--- Use your pet as long as possible! Don't rest around with a pet, but as long as he has 30% health left you should be pulling the next and slowing it. 
<br />

<br />

<br />
It's all about speed and efficiency, kill 'em fast and don't waste mana doing it.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
